######################################################################################################################
Project: Color DB
Summary:
The amazing NodeBox Color(http://nodebox.net/code/index.php/Colors#theme) by Tom De Smedt and Frederik De Bleser
library is incredibly useful, but limited in that it's implemented in Python. This project is a port of the 
Hue, Shader and Theme definitions to a collection of DB scripts that can be used in a general database. Also, there 
is an Excel representation of the values.

Author: Samuel Holloway
URL: https://github.com/sholloway/Color-DB
Source: https://github.com/sholloway/Color-DB.git
Contact: sholloway@gmail.com
Twitter: @sholloway
######################################################################################################################
BUILD REQUIREMENTS:
Ruby 1.8.7 or higher
RubyGems
roo gem
SQLite3
######################################################################################################################
RUNTIME REQUIREMENTS:
I've tested this on OS X Lion.
######################################################################################################################
Build Instructions:
In the root directory of the project simply run the command: 
> rake
This should create a directory named "output" which contains the sql file. You can then create an sqlite3 database of
your specifications by running the command:
> sqlite3 your_db_name < create_colors_db.sql

